ğŸ“¦ What is a Pod in Kubernetes?
A Pod is the most basic deployable unit in Kubernetes. It can hold one or more tightly coupled containers that share resources like storage and network.

ğŸ—ï¸ Create a Pod (Command-line):
kubectl run nginx-pod --image=nginx --restart=Never

ğŸ“„ Create a Pod (Manifest File):
nginx-pod.yaml
yaml
CopyEdit
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx-pod
spec:
  containers:
    - name: nginx
      image: nginx
      ports:
        - containerPort: 80

Create the pod:
kubectl apply -f nginx-pod.yaml

ğŸ” List Pods in Your Cluster
Once your pod is running, check the status with:
kubectl get pods

To see more details:
kubectl describe pod nginx-pod

To view logs:
kubectl logs nginx-pod
